Vintage cocktail selection found only at @thedonovanbar has been carefully curated by @cocktailmaestro himself. 

The crowning glory of the vintage menu is ‘Salvatore’s Legacy’, a cocktail that in 2012 broke the Guinness World Record for the most expensive cocktail with a Cognac-based drink priced at £5,500 a glass. 
•
Credit to @thedonovanbar 
•
Made using the bar’s oldest spirit, a 1788 Clos de Griffier Vieux cognac, as well as Dubb Orange liqueur (c1860) and a dash of Angostura Bitters (c1930), this original creation of Salvatore’s offers more than 700 years of liquid history.

On Friday, The Donovan Bar made history once again with @federico_pvn having the opportunity of preparing ‘Salvatore’s legacy’.

An amazing and historial moment for the team! 

Salute 🍸

node.text:
Celebrating Negronis week with this stunning 🤩 SUNSET NEGRONI
- 30ml/1oz Littoral Gin (gifted)
- 15ml/0.5oz Campari
- 15ml/0.5oz Cynar
- 25ml/fat 0.75oz White Vermouth
- optional: Several drops of Apple Cider Vinegar (if you like a little zing)
- - - - -
•
Credit to @servedbysoberon 
•
HOW: Stir all with ice / Pour over crushed ice in a snifter / Express orange peel & rub some thyme over the cocktail (both can be left as garnish)
- - - - -
A few weeks ago I was asked if I wanted to design a drink for the August Box of 'European Craft Club', a Germany-based monthly Gin Subscription Box.🍸 In the box you'll always find a bottle of Gin with accompanying tonic, but also a booklet, featuring some fun recipe ideas 🍹 and this month, one of those is this Sunset Negroni!
.
Littoral Gin, this month's selection, is distilled by Czernys Küstendestillerie in Germany.🇩🇪 What makes it stad out is that it features a blend of 'Land meets Sea'-flavors, featuring Apple & Blackcurrant on one side 🍏 yet Sea Lettuce, Brown Algae and Sea Wormwood on the other.⛵ This results in a Gin that can easily stand its ground in drinks that contain other bold flavors 🥃.
.
For it, I created this riff on the classic Negroni, yet splitting the bitter with Cynar for more 'depth', and subbing Sweet for White Vermouth, creating a larger stage for the Gin to dance on.🕺💃 Lastly, if you've got it, and like your drinks with a funky twist: Try adding just a couple of drops of Apple Cider Vinegar (less is more!), it'll pop on your palate 🍎!
.

Vintage cocktail selection found only at @thedonovanbar has been carefully curated by @cocktailmaestro himself. 

The crowning glory of the vintage menu is ‘Salvatore’s Legacy’, a cocktail that in 2012 broke the Guinness World Record for the most expensive cocktail with a Cognac-based drink priced at £5,500 a glass. 
•
Credit to @thedonovanbar 
•
Made using the bar’s oldest spirit, a 1788 Clos de Griffier Vieux cognac, as well as Dubb Orange liqueur (c1860) and a dash of Angostura Bitters (c1930), this original creation of Salvatore’s offers more than 700 years of liquid history.

On Friday, The Donovan Bar made history once again with @federico_pvn having the opportunity of preparing ‘Salvatore’s legacy’.

An amazing and historial moment for the team! 

Salute 🍸
